cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of recognizing weak embeddings of graphs, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications in clustering, cartography, and visualization, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper presents an algorithm that uses local operations to untangle the image of the graph, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
